Taste roasty, for some reason my mind connected with spruce to the taste. Like a cedar tree and I cannot reason not to connect it on each taste. Bit bitter...but pine, spruce, cedar is what I keep getting.

Good beer.
Pours black with thin dark brown head.  Nose is soft with hint of roasted coffee and chocolate.  Smoother finish with dark chocolate aftertaste.

Taste has very strong note of wooden cask, very different. Whiskey does come through in taste as well.

Different than any other stout so far Ive had

review_blob: Good stout with nice overtones....pours dark, drinks dark, palate is full , light after taste

Good.  Flavorful, some fruit notes.  On tap. Would drank it twiced. Cream colored yellow. Nice beverage with BBQ

A little under the weather, so I wasnt able to pick up a great deal on aroma, but I did get some roast smell...Appearance is dark brown...light head with a lingering rim ... taste of spice, lil chocolate, first taste was a medium bitter, but fades to a light bitter....maybe a bit of salt taste....fizzy...but not a overpowering finish...B+

The taste is not what I expected.  Id call it a timid to smooth taste.  Not as rich as I would expect I guess.  Aroma is stout with a hint of metal even though it came in a bottle.
No chocolate or coffee notes. More of a brown sugar.
Not bad at all though.
Yet far from the great ones.  But, to come out of Jamaica and a stout...fighting a warm weather all the time... B grade from me.

It is full, smooth, & satisfying. Excellent stout flavor, finishing smooth, creamy, and chocolate flavor is abundant; maybe a hint of mocha to it too. Aftertaste is semi-dry. 4.9% is probably a little light.  Should be more at 6.5%.

Has a slight fruit taste to it, tasted bitter/salty...body was medium, bitter/long finish, carbonation seemed soft, texture thin/slick.......to throw some describing words to it....

Overall to me...........has a strange fruit taste to me; not one I will drink again.....drank it for the experience.............experience: 3/10

Pours with an amber hue that sits below a white frothy head. Hue is clear. The aroma is of cinammon, pumpkin and lots of different spices. The flavor is spicy all the way through (allspice). Also the beer has a weird green tea flavor to it - dont know what this is. Light body, light carbonation. Not a bad beer, but just not my style.

Supple mouthfeel in my oppinion. I would build a shrine for the 90 minute (and cant wait to try the expensive 120-minute). Aroma: Ahh there they are! What I have been waiting on - hops.. grapefruit, some slight pine, banana & lemon, my mouth is watering
Absolutely great beer. Good alcohol and and it is not as thick or heavy as one may expect. Dont hesitate.
Golden color (no pun intended), very thin head that dissapates very quickly. Its a drinkable beer. I wouldnt buy a 6 pack though. Bitter end by the way.

Bottle. Pours a cloudy copper color with a thick white head, tons of lacing. The aroma is tons of rye and hops. The flavor was just awesome; a rich and bitter hop bite throughout, some bready rye flavors balance it out well. Some honey and citrus too. A semi-sweet rye finish with a touch of banana and malt. Very nice. I am starting to fall in love with Terrapin, this beer kicks ass.

An interesting mix of a traditional brown ale and an IPA. Poured to a reddish-brown with tan head, reminiscent of a brown ale, but the nose was roasted malted nuts and wood, infused with a hint of citrusy hops. Mouthfeel was medium bodied and alternated between slightly sweet and bitter. Taste was mostly the malty flavors, but with a slight aftertaste of citrus. An interesting beer, but for my money, Id rather have either a brown ale or IPA, not both at once.

Pours a clear ruby red color with a small khaki colored head. Nose id very hoppy which is very enticing to this double ipa, caramel leads in the malty backbone with citrus and touch of earthiness. Initial taste is sweet, caramel, red berries, brown sugar. Mid palate to finish displays good hop balance that clean and crisp. Slight dry finish but still good palate duration. Touch of spicines from the alcohol is also present, however still well masked. Great double IPA,but was expecing more hops especially for the name.
good stuff, nice taste, nice coloring, taste like a good beer. rock star taste
